<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              PagePadding="16"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14">

    <Section>
        <Paragraph FontSize="20" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,0,0,8">
            Setup using the charger
        </Paragraph>

        <Paragraph>
            The charge mode and charge current limit most appropriate for the battery type and capacity can also be selected using a
      Bluetooth enabled device (mobile phone or tablet) with the VictronConnect app.
        </Paragraph>

        <!-- 1st image -->
        <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
            <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon1.png"
             Stretch="Uniform"
             MaxWidth="800"/>
        </BlockUIContainer>

        <Paragraph>
            For further information about the VictronConnect app refer to the VictronConnect manual
  (
            <Hyperlink NavigateUri="Assets/Manuals/VictronConnect_Manual.pdf">open PDF</Hyperlink>
            ).
        </Paragraph>


        <Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,6">To setup using Bluetooth:</Paragraph>

        <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="0,2,0,0">
            <!-- 1 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    Download and install the VictronConnect app onto the Bluetooth enabled device (mobile phone or tablet).
          The VictronConnect app can be downloaded from:
                </Paragraph>
                <List MarkerStyle="UpperLatin" Margin="16,4,0,8">
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph>Android — Google Play Store</Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph>iOS/Mac — Apple App Store</Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                </List>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 2 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    Enable Bluetooth on the device if not already enabled, but do not attempt to pair with the Blue Smart IP22 Charger.
                </Paragraph>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 3 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    Connect the Blue Smart IP22 Charger AC power cable to a mains power outlet; after a short delay the LEDs indicating
          the current charge mode and charge state will illuminate.
                </Paragraph>
                <!-- 2nd image -->
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon2.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform"
                 MaxWidth="800"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 4 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    Open the VictronConnect app and locate the Blue Smart IP22 Charger in the Device list &quot;Local&quot; page, under &quot;Other devices&quot;.
          If it doesn’t appear, ensure Bluetooth is enabled and you are close to the charger, then tap the
                    <Bold>Scan</Bold> button
          (round orange button with circular arrow) in the bottom-right corner.
                </Paragraph>
                <!-- 3rd image -->
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon3.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform"
                 MaxWidth="800"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 5 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    Select the Blue Smart IP22 Charger from the Device list &quot;Local&quot; page, under &quot;Other devices&quot;.
                </Paragraph>
                <!-- 4th image -->
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon4.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform"
                 MaxWidth="800"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 6 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    VictronConnect will attempt to establish a Bluetooth connection with the charger and display the connection progress
          in the
                    <Bold>Connecting</Bold> pop-up dialog box.
                </Paragraph>
                <!-- 5th image -->
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon5.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform"
                 MaxWidth="800"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 7 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    On first connection to a new/unpaired device, a Bluetooth pairing request pop-up will appear; enter the default PIN code
          stated on the label on the back of the charger (or try
                    <Bold>000000</Bold> if there is no label), then select
                    <Bold>Pair</Bold> .
                </Paragraph>
                <!-- 6th image -->
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon6.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform"
                 MaxWidth="800"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 8 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    Select the
                    <Bold>Settings</Bold> icon (gear in the top-right corner) to open the Settings page.
                </Paragraph>
                <!-- 7th image -->
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon7.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform"
                 MaxWidth="800"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 9 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    From
                    <Bold>Charge preset</Bold> , choose the appropriate integrated charge mode (Normal, Normal + Recondition, High,
          High + Recondition, or Li-ion). Ensure recondition is enabled only when required, as unnecessary use reduces battery life.
                </Paragraph>
                <!-- 8th image -->
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon8.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform"
                 MaxWidth="800"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 10 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    If the maximum rated charge current is excessive, enable
                    <Bold>Low current mode</Bold> (limits charge current to 50%).
          Set this via the
                    <Bold>Charge current</Bold> menu; when enabled the
                    <Bold>NIGHT</Bold> LED will blink.
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph>
                    Alternatively, enable
                    <Bold>Night mode</Bold> to temporarily activate low current for 8 hours (to reduce fan noise).
          Toggle the
                    <Bold>Night mode</Bold> switch on; when enabled the
                    <Bold>NIGHT</Bold> LED will illuminate.
                </Paragraph>
                <!-- 9th image -->
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,12">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/viccon9.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform"
                 MaxWidth="800"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <!-- 11 -->
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    <Bold>Lock Mode Button</Bold> — When enabled, the physical mode button is locked and cannot change the charger’s configuration.
          The following functions still work:
                </Paragraph>
                <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,4,0,8">
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph>Restart charge cycle to Bulk</Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph>Enable Night mode</Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph>Reset Bluetooth</Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                </List>
                <Paragraph>
                    When locked, pressing or holding the button causes all LEDs to flash to indicate the lock is active.
                </Paragraph>
            </ListItem>
        </List>

        <Paragraph Margin="8,8,0,0">
            All settings are stored and will not be lost when the charger is disconnected from mains power or the battery.
        </Paragraph>
    </Section>
</FlowDocument>
